<span id="freeTextContainer15955859504752250045">Every poem in this collection by Nobel Laureate Ted Kooser captures such multi-sensory clarity, it felt like being transported in time and place. Only the very best of poetry does this so well. He creates visual imagery ala Ansel Adams or a painter with the technical skill of Norman Rockwell. He captures moments in words as adeptly as a skilled, veteran novelist. My bookshelves are lonely without a copy of &quot;Delights and Shadows.&quot; I&apos;m very eager to check out the rest of his work.</span>
  <span id="freeText15955859504752250045" style="display:none">Every poem in this collection by Nobel Laureate Ted Kooser captures such multi-sensory clarity, it felt like being transported in time and place. Only the very best of poetry does this so well. He creates visual imagery ala Ansel Adams or a painter with the technical skill of Norman Rockwell. He captures moments in words as adeptly as a skilled, veteran novelist. My bookshelves are lonely without a copy of "Delights and Shadows." I'm very eager to check out the rest of his work.</span>
